		<div id="aboutText">
			<p class="aboutTextHeader">Denny's DAO</p>
			<br>
			<p class="aboutTextBread">
			This is a DAO (Decentralized Autonomous Organization). It allows you to  
			create a decentralized, democratically run organization. A DAO uses 
			peer-to-peer communication for information sharing. The management and   
			processing of information (adding blog posts, updating a forum thread, changing  
			a nickname, etc.) is done through the Ethereum client. The Ethereum client makes 
			sure that everyone's local data is kept in sync, that it is kept current, 
			and that all changes the information are valid (in accordance with the 
			agreed-upon rules).
			</p>
			<p class="aboutTextBread">
			DAO's can have many different rules. They do not even have to be democratically 
			run. Rules are updated and kept current by the same mechanisms that processes the 
			other information.
			</p>
		</div>
